The ZeroedIn workforce analytics skill gives clients immediate updates and insights about their workforce from ZeroedIn using only their voice.  Any workforce insight managed by ZeroedIn can be retrieved and delivered via Alexa.  Users can specify a date period or a filter, such as a department or job title, when asking Alexa for facts and flash briefings.  ZeroedIn automatically applies user security in order to control access to sensitive information and restrict users to only the data that their company authorizes them to hear.Installation and configuration is simple.  You install the ZeroedIn skill via the Amazon Alexa app on your smartphone or tablet device.  Once installed, you must link your ZeroedIn workforce analytics user account with the ZeroedIn skill in order to use it.  To link your account, you must have your ZeroedIn user account and password ready.  Select the option to link your account.  ZeroedIn will present a login form to enter your user account and password.  Once your credentials are validated, ZeroedIn will ask you to authorize or deny access to your account via Alexa.  Choose __uthorize_.   You are now ready to use the ZeroedIn skill.Using the ZeroedIn Skill for Amazon AlexaOnce the ZeroedIn skill is installed and your account is linked, you can invoke the skill at any time by issuing one of these commands to Alexa:__pen ZeroedIn_ or __sk ZeroedIn__here are two main services supported by the ZeroedIn skill.  One is retrieving a set of key measure data points, and the other is retrieving a flash briefing.  These services are also supported by a few others, such as updating your profile with a list of valid key measures, updating your profile with a list of flash briefings, listing the key measures that are available to you, and listing the flash briefings that are available to you.For new users, you must first ask Alexa to update your profile with your key measures and flash briefings.   Issue the following command to Alexa:"Alexa, ask ZeroedIn to update my profile."Alexa will retrieve the same key measures and flash briefings that are available to you in the ZeroedIn workforce analytics suite.  To hear a list of available key measures, flash briefings, or to describe a specific key measure in more detail issue the following commands to Alexa:"Alexa, ask ZeroedIn to list my key measures.""Alexa, ask ZeroedIn to list my flash briefings.""Alexa, ask ZeroedIn to describe {title of a key measure}"  You will use the title of the key measure or flash briefing in your ultimate request to retrieve the fact or flash briefing from ZeroedIn.  For instance, if one of your key measures is "Employee Turnover", you can issue the following command to Alexa:"Alexa, ask ZeroedIn, what is Employee Turnover".By default, ZeroedIn will return data for the current monthly period.  To specify another period , use keywords such as Month, Quarter, or Year.  To specify a date, you can use short or full date notation depending on the period (e.g. June 2016; March 31, 2017; 2016).  For example, you can issue the following command to Alexa:"Alexa, ask ZeroedIn, what is Employee Turnover for the quarter ending March 31st 2018"To retrieve a flash briefing, you must first have one or more flash briefings created in ZeroedIn and available to you.  Any custom flash briefings can be created via the ZeroedIn report writer.   You must specify the title of the flash briefing in your request to Alexa.  For example, you can issue the following command to Alexa:"Alexa, ask ZeroedIn for a flash briefing on Recruiting".By default, ZeroedIn will return the flash briefing report for the current monthly period if a specific period and/or date is not specified.  Please visit the ZeroedIn customer support portal for additional instructions on using the ZeroedIn Workforce Analytics Skill for Amazon Alexa.

The organization__ mission is to advance the practice of corporate real estate through professional development opportunities, publications, research, conferences, designations and networking in 47 local chapters and networking groups globally.Corporate real estate is the real property used by a company for its own operational purposes. It provides corporations with a productive environment to house employees, manufacture and distribute products and provide services to the market. Corporate real estate touches all classes of property, land and buildings such as office facilities, data centers, manufacturing facilities, logistic centers, corporate headquarters, distribution facilities, retail stores and hotels. Corporate real estate executive members (end users/occupiers) who belong to CoreNet Global have strategic responsibility for their corporations_ total real estate footprint of owned and leased space. They are charged with anticipating and responding to a corporation__ property needs as a result of business growth, expansion or contraction. They are employed by a diverse mix of industries including high-tech, financial services, manufacturing, pharmaceutical, telecommunications, healthcare, insurance and oil and gas.  They generally manage portfolios with millions of square feet property spanning multiple continents.Virtually all corporate real estate departments partner with external service provider companies to deliver services needed to acquire, maintain and dispose of real estate. A broad range of corporate services are required to support the corporate real estate function, including but not limited to brokerage, site selection, architecture and interior design, lease administration, facilities management and technology platforms. This skill reads the BDO Forex page to provide the recent exchange rates for a list of supported currencies. It provides the same information with the Flash Briefing version (search for "BDO Forex (Flash Briefing)") and offers additional interaction to convert amount between currencies and be more accurate on the rates by specifying your own. Other currencies can be used too via In-Skill Purchasing.Disclaimer: This skill is not provided nor officially endorsed by BDO Unibank, Inc.To know the exchange rates of any currency, just ask, "What's the rate for (currency name)". There are currently 10 supported currencies:- US Dollar (free)- Japanese Yen- Euro- Hong Kong Dollar- Australian Dollar- Singaporean Dollar- Canadian Dollar- British Pound- Swiss Franc- Chinese YuanUsing the Buy and Sell Rate of any two currencies, you can use them to:- Know how much a certain amount will be worth- Know how much you'll need to obtain a specific amountTo do that, just ask, "How much is (number) point (number) (from currency) in (to currency)?"Examples:- "How much is 500 US Dollars in Japanese Yen?"- "How much is 1000 point 50 Pesos in Chinese Yuan?"If you have at least one purchased currency, you can have the option to change the Buy and Sell Rate of a currency. This is useful for scenarios when you're already at the bank and the rates had changed and no longer matched the numbers posted on the website. To do that, just say, "Change the (rate type) of (currency) to (number) point (number)"Examples:- "Change the Buy Rate of US Dollar to fifty point twenty five"You can always reset your changes to the rates by simply saying, "Reset all exchange rates". Note that all changes to the rates are automatically reset every time the skill is relaunched.Of course, at any time, you can always say the following:- "Help"- "Goodbye"Hope you find this skill useful. For questions, feedback, or suggestion, please send an email to bdo.forex@gmail.com

Get current prices of about 2000 different crypto currencies (aka Coins) in about 200 different national currencies, with aggregated data from the most popular crypto currency marketplaces. For example price of Bitcoin (BTC) in US Dollars (USD), or Ethereum (ETH) in Euros (EUR). Other popular coins supported are Litecoin (LTC), DigitalCach (DASH), Monero (XMR), Ripple (XRP) and many more! You can also save your favorite Coins, then ask for the prices of those later. You can also change your default to/output currencies: both Crypto and National currencies. You would need to link your account with the webpage https://iamcoinbot.com to take full advantage of advance functionality like: user favorites and preferences. Example usages:"Ask coin bot for the price of Bitcoin""Ask coin bot to add Bitcoin to my favorites""Ask coin bot to remove Bitcoin from my favorites""Ask coin bot for my favorites""Ask coin bot to add output Euro""Ask coin bot to remove output Euro"With currency names you can either use the ISO 3-char name (USD, EUR) or its name (Dollar, Euro). For better accuracy in cases like "Dollar" and "Pound" I would recommend to use the 3-char name of USD or GBP since there are multiple currencies that share the names Dollar and Pounds. The same goes for the Crypto Currency naming: you can use BTC or Bitcoin, ETH or Ethereum etc...CoinBot supports both speech voice as well as a visual card responses. All services related to this skill are free, based on open source technology and publicly available information from free services. CoinBot is powered by data from the awesome https://cryptocompare.com API

The Trinidad Express was founded in 1967 by a group of journalists who found themselves displaced when the British-owned __aily Mirror_ was brought out by foreign owners of the rival Guardian newspaper. They enlisted the help of a number of their country__ leading businessmen and on June 6, 1967, the first paper rolled off the presses. The popular wisdom was that it would not have lasted three months but it not only lasted but prospered. Fifty years later it is now owned by its holding company, Caribbean Caribbean Network (CCN), which also owns the country__ leading television station TV 6 and has significant holdings in a number of Caribbean media houses.A major contributor to its parent company CCN, the Express has had little trouble living up to the success of its predecessors. Founded on the precepts of good solid expository and investigative reporting it is surpassed by none in its field. Its clear and concise yet simple style reaches a wide cross-section of the Trinidad and Tobago society. The Trinidadian culture is one that is beautifully shaped by a cacophony of ethnic mixtures. The Express is the pulse of the people as it strives to reflect each of these facets by enlightening (in-depth looks into historical origins) and sensitizing (coverage of festivals) the nation to each culture that makes the society so wonderfully diversified. This type of reporting combined with a strong analysis of news and events has created a definite niche and has made the Daily Express and the Sunday Express household names.The paper has grown to an average daily readership of over 75,000 which represents over 40% of the reading population of Trinidad and Tobago. Unlike our competitors we have maintained this dominant position with a strong rate card, our advertisers supporting our market position. Its Sunday figures remain unsurpassed by the competition with the highest recorded sales in the country for the past five years _ outselling the competition by almost 8,000 copies each week. The paper aims to maximize every opportunity to become not only the choice of Trinbagonians today but to span the Caribbean.The Express web site, first published in 1997 has grown to attract a monthly audience of over a million unique visitors from all over the globe. Every day more thousands of people visit the site for news updates and events from our nation.

Now through your Echo_ or Alexa-enabled device, you can use ClearView Snap to:- Track your fleet's fuel volume and dollars spent - Identify high spend drivers and savings opportunities- Learn of exceptions, which are unusual activities that could indicate potential misuse or fraud- Get useful tips to help you manage your fleet You can move on if there's nothing new to report since you last used the skill. We__l also give you occasional tips that can help prevent problems and stay on top of any concerns that arise.Getting StartedTo hear the latest summary report about volume and spend, just say: "Alexa, ask ClearView Snap for the latest summary," or simply,"Alexa, open ClearView Snap."Setting Time PeriodThe summary report also tells you the top exceptions that were found during the last reporting period, __s-of_ the date when the report was run.  The default reporting period is one week, a rolling 7 days ending on the __s-of_ date.  You can easily change the default time period to one month, by saying:__lexa, ask ClearView Snap to change the time period_ or__lexa, ask ClearView Snap for last month__ summary.__he ClearView Snap skill will remember whatever reporting period that you last used and will use it going forward.Getting More DetailsAfter hearing the summary report and the top exceptions, you likely want more details. Try saying:__lexa, ask ClearView Snap about savings opportunities,_ or__lexa, ask ClearView Snap about potential misuse,_ or__lexa, ask ClearView Snap about exception details.__f there are multiple exceptions, you can hear them one-by-one and navigate through them by saying __ext_ or __revious._  You can also ask Alexa to repeat or start over from the beginning.When you are listening to the details of exceptions, you may want to interrupt Alexa and skip to the next exception. If you want to interrupt, you can say: __lexa, next,_ or__lexa, previous,_ or__lexa, stop.__ix Exception TypesFor the reporting time period, there are 2 exception types that could represent savings opportunities, and 4 that could represent potential misuse of gas cards by employees or indicate fraud.Savings Opportunities (where savings are $5 or more per week):1. Non-regular Fuel: Total # of non-regular grade gas purchases and associated dollars. 2. High Price Per Gallon: Total # of regular grade gas purchases with higher than average prices for the area and associated dollars.Potential Misuse:3. Multiple Transactions Per Time Period: Total # of transactions and associated dollars when an employee makes more than 1 purchase within any 15 minute increment of time.4. Exceeding Tank Capacity: Total dollar value associated with transactions that exceeded the tank capacity for the vehicle.5. Fuel Mismatch: Total # transactions and associated dollars when the type of fuel purchased isn__ the type of fuel required for the vehicle__ engine.6. Weekend Fueling: total # of transactions and associated dollars where employees or vehicles were fueled on a Saturday and Sunday.If you only want to drill into the details of a specific exception type, you can say:__lexa, ask ClearView Snap for my non-regular fuel exceptions.___lexa, ask ClearView Snap for my high price per gallon exceptions.___lexa, ask ClearView Snap for my multiple transactions exceptions.___lexa, ask ClearView Snap for my exceeding tank capacity exceptions.___lexa, ask ClearView Snap for my fuel mismatch exceptions.___lexa, ask ClearView Snap for my weekend fueling exceptions.__t any time, if you want to navigate to an area of interest, or if you want to hear the summary report and more details again, just say:__lexa, ask ClearView Snap for help.__ome back every week to check on your fleet__ fuel program performance and your employees_ fuel purchasing behavior.

Tiffany launched Shop-Eat-Surf.com in August 2007 to share the action sports industry news she was finding after taking a voluntary buyout at the Orange County Register to spend more time with her young son. She worked there 10 years as a reporter and editor.Andrew joined Shop-eat-surf.com in April 2008 after a long career in newspaper reporting, editing, and management.We strive to post at least one story and multiple industry press releases every business day, usually delivered to eNewsletter subscribers_ inboxes in the early a.m. The feedback on the site has been gratifying, and propels us out of bed early each morning to tackle the next story.Readers have asked a lot of questions about the site. Here__ more information:The goalTo provide a daily news service for action sports executives. Using our skills as a professional business journalists and editors, we tailor our content to provide timely news and insights for this fast-moving and unique industry.Our backgroundsTiffany worked as a print journalist for 13 years, mostly at the Orange County Register. Thanks to technology, she was able to utilize her journalism skills online to launch her own venture.She enjoys writing and learning about how people follow their passions to build multi-million- and multi-billion-dollar, global companies from the ground up.While she launched the site on her own, the team has grown to include Andrew Horan; Magda Hernandez, who posts press releases to our Industry Releases section; Ginny Mumm, a copy editor who also oversees our content marketing on the Industry Insight page; Sarah Brown-Cohen, who splits her time between covering swim and providing customer service to our members; and Caroline King, account executive for our Industry Careers leadership job listings section.The Shop-Eat-Surf nameTiffany originally thought she would write about her three reporting specialties _ the business of restaurants, retail and surf brands. The positive response from the action sports industry led her to narrow the focus to provide the most complete report.Executive EditionYour membership subscription gives you access to articles and podcasts reported by our team that go beyond the news of the day _ in-depth earnings reports, CEO interviews, brand and retail trends _ plus other benefits and member rewards.Independent news sourceYour subscription allows us to deliver in-depth industry business news free from conflict: we don__ accept advertising from industry brands and retailers, we don__ accept free product, and we pay our own way to trade shows, industry events and reporting trips across the U.S., Canada, Australia and Europe.Beyond the press releaseLots of sites run press releases. We try to add value as much as possible. Usually, that means asking more questions or striving for additional business insight.Submit your press releaseWe run lots of press releases, too, in our Industry Releases section. A few guidelines: Please send us your release in a Word document or in the body of your email, along with your photos. Please be sure to identify the people in the photos you send, so they__e easily found in our photo search tool.Reader postsWe are always open to reader feedback. We__l listen to anybody__ ideas, suggestions and vents. But we try to have an even-handed, measured tone on the site. We don__ like mean-spirited, anonymous postings _ even if it drives traffic. The goal is to provide straight-ahead reporting.SponsorshipsWe offer sponsorships to companies serving the action sports industry, but we do not accept sponsorships from brands or retailers in the sector, to avoid potential or perceived conflicts between sponsorship and stories on the site.Sponsorships are branding opportunities. They keep your business name, products, and services in front of our audience of influential, affluent, coastal executives and entrepreneurs.

iEnterprise CRM (iCRM) from iEnterprises is a unique CRM solution that leverages artificial intelligence to provide a full Customer Relationship Management (CRM) experience VIA voice control.  iCRM can help your entire small business stay organized and sell more. This skill requires that you sign up for iCRM.  iCRM is free for up to two users and you can sign up at http://ienterprises.com/icrm/ or you can click the link on the login page that shows when installing the iCRM skill.  In addition to voice control iCRM can be used VIA a web browser, mobile app or a mac OS app.  We recommend that you first login to iCRM VIA a web browser to customize iCRM and import your data.  Once iCRM is setup then this Alexa skill is very useful for reading and updating various items in iCRM using only your voice.   Once the iCRM skill is installed you can use your voice to control various aspects of the solution. Some examples are below.  To get your latest leads say __lexa ask iCRM to get new leads_.  Note that this presumes that you have already created some leads in iCRM.  To get the number of accounts from iCRM simply say __lexa ask iCRM to get the total number of accounts__t is recommended that you start a conversation or discussion with iCRM VIA Alexa to perform more complex operations.  To start a conversation with iCRM simply say __lexa Launch iCRM_ or __lexa talk to iCRM_. Once the iCRM conversation is started you can just speak the commands you would like iCRM and Alexa to perform without having to mention Alexa or iCRM in each dialog.  Examples of conversations are below.  Remember you just first say Alexa Launch iCRM_ or __lexa talk to iCRM_ to start conversations like the ones in the examples below.  Note that all of the examples below presume that you already have already created or imported data into iCRM.  To create a follow-up reminder, say, __reate follow up__lexa will then ask for the account or person__ name you would like to be reminded about. Say the name of the account or person. Once the item is found by Alexa it will ask for the date of the follow up.  Say the date you would to have iCRM remind you.  For example, __anuary 1 2018_.  Alexa will then as for the time you would like to be reminded.  Say the time.  For example, __leven AM_ Finally Alexa will ask for follow up comments.  Say the follow up comments.  For example, __all them and ask them for the order_. To read any data from iCRM say __et data_ or __ead Data_.  Alexa will then ask for the name of the module you would like to get data from.  Say the name of the module.  For example, __ccounts_.  Alexa will then ask for the name of the field you would like to retrive.  Say the name of the field.  For example, __tatus_.  Alexa will then tell you the value for that field.  To update any text data from iCRM say __et data_ or __pdate Data_.  Alexa will then ask for the name of the module you would like to update.  Say the name of the module.  For example, __ccounts_.  Alexa will then ask for the name of the field you would like to update.  Say the name of the field.  For example, __ame_.  Alexa will then ask for the value for the field you would like to update.  Say the new name of the account.  For example, __Enterprises_.  The above example changes the name of your account to __Enterprises_.  Note that currently update is only supported on text fields.  We hope to support all field types for update in the future.
